<br>
About the effectiveness of specing in Battlesongs:<br>
For instance, one spec I'm currently considering is 39 Axe/39 Songs/36 Parry, and I was wondering if the 3 extra points in Songs really makes a difference, seeing that you get nothing specing from 35-41. Would 39 Axe/39 Parry/36 Songs be better than the first spec?<br>
<br>
If speccing to 39 in Battlesongs isn't really worth it, does anyone thing specing 44 Axe/35 Songs/34 Parry would be worthwhile?<br>
<br>
Also this character in on Gaheris, where I do have a character for most of the other hybrids, and I'm playing this character for fun, not to have the best character. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kjeld>Kjeld</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Fervent</span><br>  Posts: 202<br> <font color=#ff0000>(1/23/03 8:32 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=465.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Hmmm</span><hr size=1> This specialization could be valid in the Gaheris server, when you'll be sure you will not get engaged in any PvP of any type.<br>
<br>
In a regular RvR or full PVP server, not going 43 battlesong is self destructive. <br>
A lot of skald now will say that the skald in RvR has devolved into a glorified &quot;speed bot&quot;. Some will say that the skald can be a valid fighter and/or utility fighter, but they will not neglect speed 5 in any case. There is no doubt about a skald beeing *expected* to have speed 5 in group, and, considering other realm's speed, snaring, end/sprinting abilities, you can not really do well, grouped or solo, as a skald, with speed 4. The speed song is an abiltiy for which we &quot;pay&quot; a lot in terms of class balance. Without speed, the skald, is, plainly put, gimpy. <br>
<br>
Now, your situation is kinda different, because in Gaheris, there is no RvR endgame, and no monster that you can't evade or run from with speed 4. Which is also more than enough to get your group from point A to point B, with the help of the pretty extensive medaillon/TP system.<br>
<br>
So I guess your spec could work fine in Gaheris. Though in such a strict PvE environment, Paladins, Wardens, Bards or other similar melee/support classes will be much more useful than a skald. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showPrevMessage?topicID=465.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showNextMessage?topicID=465.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=465.topic&index=1><img src=http://www.stuckathome.com/skalded/images/addreply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.emailToFriend?topicID=465.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.threadControl?topicID=465.topic><img src=http://www.stuckathome.com/skalded/images/closethread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=465.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/subscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to receive email notification of replies"> Click to receive email notification of replies</a> <br>  <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=465.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/unsubscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to stop receiving email notification of replies"> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies</a> <br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub36.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowFor